Title: The Light Cone in String Theory
Author: Emil Martinec
Comments: 9 pages; some minor errors corrected; discussion section expanded
Report-no: EFI-91-23
Journal-ref: Class.Quant.Grav. 10 (1993) L187-L192
\\
  The causal boundary of string propagation -- defined as the hypersurface in
loop space bordering the timelike(spacelike) domains in which two successive
measurements of the string field do(do not) interfere with one another -- is
argued to be $0=\int d\sigma\bigl(\delta X(\sigma)\bigr)^2 =
  \sum_{\ell=-\infty}^\infty \delta x^\mu_{-\ell}\delta x_{\mu \ell}.$ Some
possible consequences are discussed.
